about.description: Bringing the elegance of C# EventHandler to Python
about.summary: Python Event Handling the C# Style

name: events
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "Events" %}
{% set version = "0.3" %}
{% set sha256 = "f4d9c41a5c160ce504278f219fe56f44242ca63794a0ad638b52d1e087ac2a41" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: {{ sha256 }}

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: python -m pip install --no-deps --ignore-installed .

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - pip

  run:
    - python

test:
  imports:
    - events

about:
  home: http://github.com/pyeve/events
  license: BSD-3-Clause
  license_family: BSD
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'Python Event Handling the C# Style'
  description: |
    Bringing the elegance of C# EventHandler to Python
  doc_url: https://events.readthedocs.org
  dev_url: http://github.com/pyeve/events

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - holgern
